
=> List all currently running services: This command filters the list to show only services in the 'running' sub-state:

  #systemctl list-units --type=service --state=running

=> List all active services: This includes services that are running or have exited but are still considered 'active' by systemd:

  #systemctl list-units --type=service --state=active

=> Check the status of a specific service: Replace service_name (e.g., ssh, apache2) with the actual name of the service you want to check:

  # systemctl status service_name
